1. truffle-config.js :
  First you need to configure Truffle to connect to Ganache. 
  Open the truffle-config.js file for editing and locate the networks section (around line 38).

2.You need to uncomment the development section and set the parameters to match Ganache settings.

Ganache displays itâ€™s host and port number in the main interface. For example:

Host: 127.0.0.1
Port: 7545

3. In truffle-config.js uncomment the development section. 
Set the host and port values to match Ganache, then save the file.
